@startuml
title ML-KEM key establishment (one message)
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

participant "Alice\n(key owner)" as A
participant "Bob\n(encapsulator)" as B

== Setup ==
A -> A : (ek, dk) = ML-KEM.KeyGen()
A -> B : encapsulation key ek (public)

== Encapsulation ==
B -> B : (K, c) = ML-KEM.Encaps(ek)\nK = fresh 256-bit shared secret
B -> A : ciphertext c

== Decapsulation ==
A -> A : K' = ML-KEM.Decaps(dk, c)

note over A, B
  K' == K : both sides now hold the
  same 256-bit shared secret key.
  Use it directly for symmetric crypto.
end note
@enduml
